Program: The Why Factor
Title: Copying Art
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03x37yr
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 13 Jun 2016
Why do people try to create old masters and modern art, brush stroke by brush stroke? And, why do people buy them? He talks to art copier David Henty, fine art expert and gallery owner Philip Mould, Paul Dong a Beijing based art auctioneer, Colette Loll founder and director of the Washington-based Art Fraud Insights and art copy customer Patricia Burns from Canada. (Photo: A copy of Pablo Picasso's The Weeping Woman painted by David Henty, courtesy of the artist D.Henty) Show less